body:
I&#039;ve been playing League of Legends for a while, and Akali is one of my favourite champions. During a game today, I was playing against a Soraka, and noticed something. There are no viable items to build on a mana-less champion that give grevious wounds or another method of countering healing champions, and I&#039;m writing to enquire if something might be done about this. Liandries doesn&#039;t really cout because it&#039;s health percentage, not grevious wounds :~). I know it&#039;s a big ask, and that I&#039;m just one person, but I feel that it&#039;d be a good thing to do to balance the game. Cheers for reading lads and ladies, glhf.
